[recto] Ad [Addendum] 64. Witt Library. P.B.II: Massacre (not a combination of known motifs of PBI, but real new invention) of the Innocents. The other composition with the woman running away on the right. The great numbers of copies without alterations speaks for PBI; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. most probably based on comp. of P.B.I: 1) Antwerp Mus., N° 832, Ph. Bruckmann; 2) Hampton Court Ph.; 3) Hogskola (?= University) Stockholm; 4) Achenbach Sale, Lepke, Berlin 17.XI.1910, N° 170, Holz 70 x 106 cm; 5) Weber Sale, Fievez, Brussels 7-8 July 1926, N° 31, Copper 40 x 52 cm; [verso] 6) Rouse ? Sale, Bangel, Frankfurt 16.XII. 1927, N° 9, Holz 92,5 x 125,5 cm. The same again Sale American Art Ass. N.York, 22.I.1931, N° 68, Panel 361/2 x 451/2 in, both with authentication by Hofstede de Groot; 7) Goidsenhoven Sale, Fievez, Brussels, 17 Dec. 1930, N° 740, Bois 71 x 121 cm.
